│ non-PHI/Dbg/Alloca instruction. In malformed or edge cases (e.g., empty       │
│ blocks, blocks with only PHIs/Dbg/Allocas, or blocks constructed in unusual   │
│ address spaces), getTerminator() can return null or accessing ilist internals │
│ may trip UB if the parent pointer is invalid or the list empty.\n\n2.         │
│ Analyzing opt's Log:\n- The debug log shows SLP is analyzing PHI bundles and  │
