│ (CheckPredecessors).\n- The first transformation point identified is          │
│ BasicBlock::getTerminator() during getSpillCost. The relevant code calls:\n   │
│ * CheckForNonVecCallsInSameBlock(&*BB->getFirstNonPHIOrDbgOrAlloca(),         │
│ BB->getTerminator())\n  * OpLastInst = OpParent->getTerminator()\n  *         │
│ CheckForNonVecCallsInSameBlock(OpLastInst,                                    │
│ OpParent->getTerminator())\n\nThese calls assume both the first non-PHI       │
│ instruction and the terminator exist. If either is missing (e.g., empty       │
│ block), dereferencing leads to a crash.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe root  │
│ cause is missing defensive checks around getTerminator() and                  │
│ getFirstNonPHIOrDbgOrAlloca() in the cost analysis path. When encountering    │
│ certain CFG patterns (including blocks reached via PHI incoming edges or      │
│ predecessor traversal), blocks may be empty or contain no non-PHI/Dbg/Alloca  │
